e" data-attr="zoom" data-val="auto" data-toggle="false" data-gravity="n"><svg viewBox="0 0 1000 1000" class="icon" height="1em" width="1em"><path d="m250 850l-187 0-63 0 0-62 0-188 63 0 0 188 187 0 0 62z m688 0l-188 0 0-62 188 0 0-188 62 0 0 188 0 62-62 0z m-875-938l0 188-63 0 0-188 0-62 63 0 187 0 0 62-187 0z m875 188l0-188-188 0 0-62 188 0 62 0 0 62 0 188-62 0z m-125 188l-1 0-93-94-156 156 156 156 92-93 2 0 0 250-250 0 0-2 93-92-156-156-156 156 94 92 0 2-250 0 0-250 0 0 93 93 157-156-157-156-93 94 0 0 0-250 250 0 0 0-94 93 156 157 156-157-93-93 0 0 250 0 0 250z" transform="matrix(1 0 0 -1 0 850)"></path></svg></a></div><div class="modebar-group"><a rel="tooltip" class="modebar-btn" data-title="Show closest data on hover" data-attr="hovermode" data-val="closest" data-toggle="false" data-gravity="ne"><svg viewBox="0 0 1500 1000" class="icon" height="1em" width="1em"><path d="m375 725l0 0-375-375 375-374 0-1 1125 0 0 750-1125 0z" transform="matrix(1 0 0 -1 0 850)"></path></svg></a><a rel="tooltip" class="modebar-btn active" data-title="Compare data on hover" data-attr="hovermode" data-val="x" data-toggle="false" data-gravity="ne"><svg viewBox="0 0 1125 1000" class="icon" height="1em" width="1em"><path d="m187 786l0 2-187-188 188-187 0 0 937 0 0 373-938 0z m0-499l0 1-187-188 188-188 0 0 937 0 0 376-938-1z" transform="matrix(1 0 0 -1 0 850)"></path></svg></a></div></div></div><svg class="main-svg" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" width="348.33333333333337" height="378.33333333333337"><g class="hoverlayer"></g></svg></div></div></div></foreignObject></g><text class="draggable" name="text" x="236" y="26" r="0" rtemp="0" transform="rotate(0 236 26)" style="fill: rgb(255, 123, 0); font-weight: bold; font-style: normal; font-size: 13px; font-family: normal;">out</text><text class="draggable" name="text" x="68" y="26" r="0" rtemp="0" transform="rotate(0 68 26)" style="fill: rgb(255, 123, 0); font-weight: bold; font-style: normal; font-size: 13px; font-family: normal;">in</text><g transform="translate(327,17)" x="327" y="17" title="codeHTML" width="443" height="383" class="codeHTML" name="codeHTML" rot="0"><foreignObject x="0" y="0" width="222" height="200" style="height: 638.333px; width: 738.333px;"><div name="htmlCode" style="zoom: 60%; height: 638.333px; width: 738.333px;" code="<div class=&quot;ch&quot;>
    
    <h1>Series RLC Band-Pass Filter - SPICE AC Analysis</h1>

    <div class=&quot;ch-card&quot;>
        <h2>Circuit Components</h2>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Capacitor (C1):</strong> 1 &amp;micro;F</li>
            <li><strong>Inductor (L1):</strong> 10 mH</li>
            <li><strong>Resistor (R1):</strong> 10 &amp;Omega;</li>
            <li><strong>Input (V1):</strong> AC Voltage Source (1V amplitude)</li>
            <li><strong>Output:</strong> Taken across resistor R1</li>
        </ul>
    </div>

    <h2>Resonant Frequency</h2>
    <div class=&quot;ch-formula&quot;>
        fr = 1 / (2&amp;pi;&amp;radic;(LC)) = 1 / (2&amp;pi;&amp;radic;(10&amp;times;10&amp;minus;3 &amp;times; 1&amp;times;10&amp;minus;6)) &amp;approx; <strong>1592 Hz</strong>
    </div>

    <h2>Quality Factor &amp; Bandwidth</h2>
    <div class=&quot;ch-formula&quot;>
        Q = (1/R)&amp;radic;(L/C) = (1/10)&amp;radic;(10&amp;times;10&amp;minus;3 / 1&amp;times;10&amp;minus;6) = <strong>10</strong><br>
        BW = fr / Q = 1592 / 10 &amp;approx; <strong>159 Hz</strong>
    </div>

    <h2>Simulation Results</h2>
    <div class=&quot;ch-grid&quot;>

        <div class=&quot;ch-col blue&quot;>
            <h3>Magnitude Response (Black Line)</h3>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Below fr:</strong> Attenuation increases as frequency decreases (-20 dB/decade)</li>
                <li><strong>At Resonance (1592 Hz):</strong> Peak at 0 dB (maximum output)</li>
                <li><strong>Above fr:</strong> Attenuation increases as frequency increases (-20 dB/decade)</li>
                <li><strong>Bandwidth:</strong> Passes frequencies around 1592 Hz (&amp;plusmn;80 Hz)</li>
                <li>At resonance: XL = XC, circuit is purely resistive</li>
            </ul>
        </div>

        <div class=&quot;ch-col red&quot;>
            <h3>Phase Response (Red Line)</h3>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Low Freq (f &amp;lt; fr):</strong> +&amp;pi;/2 rad (+90&amp;deg;) - capacitive behavior</li>
                <li><strong>At Resonance:</strong> 0 rad (0&amp;deg;) - purely resistive</li>
                <li><strong>High Freq (f &amp;gt; fr):</strong> -&amp;pi;/2 rad (-90&amp;deg;) - inductive behavior</li>
                <li>Sharp phase transition around resonant frequency</li>
                <li>High Q factor causes steep phase change</li>
            </ul>
        </div>

    </div>

    <div class=&quot;ch-card green-border&quot;>
        <h2>Conclusion</h2>
        <p style=&quot;line-height: 1.6; margin: 0;&quot;>The circuit functions as a <strong>band-pass filter</strong> with a resonant frequency of approximately 1592 Hz. At resonance, the inductive and capacitive reactances cancel each other (XL = XC), leaving only the resistance. This results in maximum current flow and maximum voltage across R1. The circuit selectively passes frequencies near the resonant frequency while attenuating both lower and higher frequencies. The quality factor Q=10 indicates a relatively narrow bandwidth and sharp resonance peak.</p>
    </div>

    <div class=&quot;ch-card&quot; style=&quot;background-color: #e8f8f5; border-left: 4px solid #1abc9c;&quot;>
        <h2 style=&quot;color: #16a085;&quot;>Circuit Behavior Analysis</h2>
        <ul style=&quot;line-height: 1.6; margin: 0;&quot;>
            <li><strong>Below resonance:</strong> Capacitor dominates (high impedance), blocks low frequencies</li>
            <li><strong>At resonance:</strong> L and C cancel, minimum impedance (Z = R = 10&amp;Omega;), maximum current</li>
            <li><strong>Above resonance:</strong> Inductor dominates (high impedance), blocks high frequencies</li>
            <li><strong>Applications:</strong> Radio tuning, frequency selection, audio equalization</li>
        </ul>
    </div>

</div>"><div class="ch">
    
    <h1>Series RLC Band-Pass Filter - SPICE AC Analysis</h1>

    <div class="ch-card">
        <h2>Circuit Components</h2>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Capacitor (C1):</strong> 1 µF</li>
            <li><strong>Inductor (L1):</strong> 10 mH</li>
            <li><strong>Resistor (R1):</strong> 10 Ω</li>
            <li><strong>Input (V1):</strong> AC Voltage Source (1V amplitude)</li>
            <li><strong>Output:</strong> Taken across resistor R1</li>
        </ul>
    </div>

    <h2>Resonant Frequency</h2>
    <div class="ch-formula">
        fr = 1 / (2π√(LC)) = 1 / (2π√(10×10−3 × 1×10−6)) ≈ <strong>1592 Hz</strong>
    </div>

    <h2>Quality Factor &amp; Bandwidth</h2>
    <div class="ch-formula">
        Q = (1/R)√(L/C) = (1/10)√(10×10−3 / 1×10−6) = <strong>10</strong><br>
        BW = fr / Q = 1592 / 10 ≈ <strong>159 Hz</strong>
    </div>

    <h2>Simulation Results</h2>
    <div class="ch-grid">

        <div class="ch-col blue">
            <h3>Magnitude Response (Black Line)</h3>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Below fr:</strong> Attenuation increases as frequency decreases (-20 dB/decade)</li>
                <li><strong>At Resonance (1592 Hz):</strong> Peak at 0 dB (maximum output)</li>
                <li><strong>Above fr:</strong> Attenuation increases as frequency increases (-20 dB/decade)</li>
                <li><strong>Bandwidth:</strong> Passes frequencies around 1592 Hz (±80 Hz)</li>
                <li>At resonance: XL = XC, circuit is purely resistive</li>
            </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="ch-col red">
            <h3>Phase Response (Red Line)</h3>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Low Freq (f &lt; fr):</strong> +π/2 rad (+90°) - capacitive behavior</li>
                <li><strong>At Resonance:</strong> 0 rad (0°) - purely resistive</li>
                <li><strong>High Freq (f &gt; fr):</strong> -π/2 rad (-90°) - inductive behavior</li>
                <li>Sharp phase transition around resonant frequency</li>
                <li>High Q factor causes steep phase change</li>
            </ul>
        </div>

    </div>

    <div class="ch-card green-border">
        <h2>Conclusion</h2>
        <p style="line-height: 1.6; margin: 0;">The circuit functions as a <strong>band-pass filter</strong> with a resonant frequency of approximately 1592 Hz. At resonance, the inductive and capacitive reactances cancel each other (XL = XC), leaving only the resistance. This results in maximum current flow and maximum voltage across R1. The circuit selectively passes frequencies near the resonant frequency while attenuating both lower and higher frequencies. The quality factor Q=10 indicates a relatively narrow bandwidth and sharp resonance peak.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="ch-card" style="background-color: #e8f8f5; border-left: 4px solid #1abc9c;">
        <h2 style="color: #16a085;">Circuit Behavior Analysis</h2>
        <ul style="line-height: 1.6; margin: 0;">
            <li><strong>Below resonance:</strong> Capacitor dominates (high impedance), blocks low frequencies</li>
            <li><strong>At resonance:</strong> L and C cancel, minimum impedance (Z = R = 10Ω), maximum current</li>
            <li><strong>Above resonance:</strong> Inductor dominates (high impedance), blocks high frequencies</li>
            <li><strong>Applications:</strong> Radio tuning, frequency selection, audio equalization</li>
        </ul>
    </div>

</div></div></foreignObject></g><g x="160" y="15" transform="translate(160,15)" width="55" height="30" class="part" name="part" xo="0" yo="0" sref="L1" directory="Basic" liblocale="true" symbolfile="Inductor" model="Inductor"><g width="200" top="125" left="0" height="200" version="0.0.1" zoom="10.399999999999993" reference="L" description="{&quot;webPage&quot;:&quot;https://pyams.sf.net/doc/Elements/Basic/Inductor.html&quot;,&quot;info&quot;:&quot;&quot;}" symbolname="Inductor" device="std" type="null" model="Inductor" modelname="Inductor" modeltype="SPICE" destination="local"></g><g points="5,15 15,15" class="polyline" name="pin" type="simple" netid="4" netidpos="0" netId="4" netIdPos="0"><polyline points="5,15 15,15 " style="stroke: rgb(255, 0, 0); stroke-width: 1px;"></polyline><rect width="6" height="6" class="pin" x="2" y="12" style="stroke: rgb(0, 255, 0); fill: rgb(255, 0, 0); stroke-width: 1px; display: none;"></rect><text r="0" x="17" y="17" transform="rotate(0 17 17)" style="font-size: 12px; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; display: none; fill: rgb(0, 0, 0);">p</text><text r="0" x="5" y="15" transform="rotate(0 5 15)" style="font-size: 12px; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; display: none;">+</text><ellipse cx="13.5" cy="15" rx="1.5" ry="1.5" style="stroke: rgb(255, 0, 0); fill: rgb(255, 0, 0); stroke-width: 1px; display: none;"></ellipse><polygon points="15,13.5 15,16.5 16.5,15 " style="stroke: rgb(255, 0, 0); fill: rgb(255, 0, 0); stroke-width: 1px; display: none;"></polygon></g><g points="55,15 45,15" class="polyline" name="pin" type="simple" netid="0" netidpos="0" netId="0" netIdPos="0"><polyline points="55,15 45,15 " style="stroke: rgb(255, 0, 0); stroke-width: 1px;"></polyline><rect width="6" height="6" class="pin" x="52" y="12" style="stroke: rgb(0, 255, 0); fill: none; stroke-width: 1px; display: none;"></rect><text r="0" x="43" y="17" transform="rotate(0 43 17)" style="font-size: 12px; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; dis